The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 86.06 points, or 0.20%, to 43,828.06, the S&P 500 lost 0.16 point, or 0.00%, to 6,051.09 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 23.88 points, or 0.12%, to 19,926.72.

items.title: Live: Will Nifty Make An Attempt To Reclaim 25,000 This Week? US Fed Decision Awaited| Opening Bell
items.description:
In a highly volatile session on December 13, the Indian equity indices made a sharp recovery from the day's low and ended strong led by auto, bank, telecom and FMCG names. BSE Sensex and Nifty50 bounced back more than 2 percent from the day's low amid ease in retail inflation and three-month high industrial growth at 3.5 percent in October.

At close, the Sensex was up 843.16 points or 1.04 percent at 82,133.12, and the Nifty was up 219.60 points or 0.89 percent at 24,768.30. This morning GIFT Nifty is hinting at a negative start.
